name: Meet Elizabeth Bartusiak
body:
# So, Who IS Elizabeth, Anyway? # ![](https://scontent-ord1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpt1/v/t1.0-9/10375492_1485615991713376_1411056303023213371_n.jpg?oh=f9e34e3bfce4286a39fde897109745a0&oe=5614141A) Hello! My name is Elizabeth Bartusiak. My favorite colors are orange and yellow because they are so bright and happy! Something you would not guess by looking at me is that I love to play basketball. Consequently, I am also a big fan of the Chicago Bulls. I play the violin and love to practice often. Last year, I even played for a wedding! Aside from running on the basketball court and making music, I love math. To me, math is like solving complex problems using nothing but a little bit of hope and a lot of shear logic! In the future, you will find me working with computer science to protect other people's cyber-security. This is my rendition of a painting by Jackson Pollock: ![](https://scontent-ord1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xta1/v/t1.0-9/11825971_1433011730362531_1447994703077333653_n.jpg?oh=9c51179499e03a1aa47b11a9185de2ee&oe=564C3400) Mr. Pollock likes this painting! Look at his smile! ![](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-hevH-jV5W8w/ThO6LwlvRdI/AAAAAAAADwY/X0qceV5fQ5o/s400/Screen%2Bshot%2B2011-07-02%2Bat%2B11.56.20%2BPM.png) To create your own Jackson Pollock painting and allow your creative juices to flow, click the following link:

What is a city you ask? Well, I made a city skyline just for you.
